netopeer_sysrepo
----------------

To run this example NETCONF server and allow
it to manage a datastore, follow these steps,
in order:


Compilation
~~~~~~~~~~~

1. north_client

$ ./configure --with-sysrepod=<path-to-sysrepod-repository>
$ make
# make install

2. south_client

$ make


Running
~~~~~~~

You need 3 separate terminals:

1. sysrepod

(start sysrepod with default options - no argument needed)

2. south_client

$ ./sysrepod_ifc_daemon

3. noth_client

# netopeer-sysrepo


Now you can connect to netopeer-sysrepo, it
acts as a standard NETCONF server.
